    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-01-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-01-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="541"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d541">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian Pauncefote</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-01-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 30, 1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: All the details of the Behring Sea arbitration
                    having now been finally settled by the understanding arrived at as to the
                    governments who shall be invited to select the three foreign arbitrators, I have
                    the honor to request you to be good enough to inform me whether you are prepared
                    to proceed at once to the preparation and signature of the formal arbitration
                    convention and of the joint commission agreement, in accordance with the text of
                    the articles to be inserted therein which was signed by us on the 18th December
                    last.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian Pauncefote</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
